cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE. 

The paper deals with runtime assurance for neural controllers of complex autonomous and cyber-physical systems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the design, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also involves reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the case studies involving a ground rover and an artificial pancreas system suggest that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
